(273, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/umlgyjF8rs8/wordpress-nostalgia'' title=''As we inch closer towards the 10 year anniversary of WordPress, I’ve been browsing through a few different time capsule posts. Some of them really tap into my nostalgic center while others have me asking questions such as, what ever happened to the Flock browser that WordPress was excited about in 2005? It was described as being just like FireFox but with go [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: WordPress Nostalgia</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2013/05/22/james-banks-mobile-first-development-and-design-for-wordpress/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: James Banks: Mobile First Development and Design for WordPress</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/OeENyG5J5qs/help-ithemes-help-their-neighbors'' title=''iThemes, the company behind products such as BackupBuddy and the Builder theme are reporting that their headquarters as well as all of their staff are ok following the Tornadoes that ripped Moore, Oklahoma apart on May 20th. Not only has their company donated $2,000.00 to the Red Cross for relief efforts, but they are asking everyone to consider texting REDC [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: Help iThemes Help Their Neighbors</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WordpressTavern/~3/60XdX6380Vo/user-guide-how-to-choose-a-plugin'' title=''One of the best things about WordPress is its third-party ecosystem of themes and plugins. If WordPress doesn’t have the feature set you need out of the box, chances are very good that with just a few plugins, you can make the WordPress of your dreams. However, to new and veteran users alike, choosing which plugins to install is not always an easy task. Usin [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: User Guide – How To Choose A Plugin</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2013/05/21/tom-mcfarlin-a-discussion-and-introduction-to-wordpress-plugins/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Tom McFarlin: A Discussion and Introduction To WordPress Plugins</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
